href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A deductive system <fr:tex>\mathcal {D}</fr:tex> is given by a type <fr:tex>\mathbf {ob} _{ \mathcal {D} }</fr:tex> of “objects”, and for every pair <fr:tex>A,B \in \mathbf {ob} _{ \mathcal {D} }</fr:tex> a set <fr:tex>\mathbf {hom} _{ \mathcal {D} } { \mathopen {} \left ( A , B \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex> of <fr:em>morphisms</fr:em>, together with cut and identity laws:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li><fr:strong>cut:</fr:strong> for each <fr:tex>A,B,C \in \mathbf {ob} _{ \mathcal {D} }</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>f \in   \mathbf {hom} _{ \mathcal {D} } { \mathopen {} \left ( A , B \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>g \in \mathbf {hom} _{ \mathcal {D} } { \mathopen {} \left ( B , C \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>, a morphism <fr:tex>f;g \in \mathbf {hom} _{ \mathcal {D} } { \mathopen {} \left ( A , C \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>.</fr:li>
  
  <fr:li><fr:strong>identity:</fr:strong> for each <fr:tex>A \in \mathbf {ob} _{ \mathcal {D} }</fr:tex>, a morphism <fr:tex>1 _{ A } \in \mathbf {hom} _{ \mathcal {D} } { \mathopen {} \left ( A , A \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex> such that <fr:tex>1 _{ A } ;f = f</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>f;1 _{ B }</fr:tex> for each <fr:tex>f \in \mathbf {hom} _{ \mathcal {D} } { \mathopen {} \left ( A , B \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:related><fr:backlinks><fr:tree
